    {
      "id": "82506473c6915544e7b173e64f7eeeb259c7c00f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-05-01 06:23:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(3 comments)\n\nPer discussion on the call, the implementation of this patch will change somewhat.  Also, some minor comments on the patch itself.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "317d8199fb7ab4c3d1e779419966b08914cd16f8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-27 09:11:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(8 comments)\n\nKit, any plans to refresh this?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "b261cf836b5a2161b5b3d24a6c10b067ff9ce5fa",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 269,
        "name": "Kit Westneat",
        "email": "kit.westneat@gmail.com",
        "username": "kitwestneat"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-27 21:48:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThanks for reminding me about this patch, I had forgotten it was separate from the other one. Is there a reason to keep it separate? If we do keep it separate, could we land the test patch without ACL support and then add the ACL tests as part of this patch?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "2bd9e43962b5adf91ff09f8eb9bfbf60cdd56d09",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-27 22:50:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThere is no reason to keep it separate from the main nodemap patch. I think it was just developed separately. That said, if the first part of the patch is ready to land, there is no need to refresh it just to merge in the ACL mapping. It can also land separately.\n\nThat said, it would be great to run the ACL tests (currently called from sanity.sh) again with UID mapping enabled to verify that functionality.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "f1fd662919a873944f920d692d4380348e33fca8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 269,
        "name": "Kit Westneat",
        "email": "kit.westneat@gmail.com",
        "username": "kitwestneat"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-29 17:49:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nIt ended up making more sense to me to merge it into the other patch. The nodemaps and ACLs don't really work at all together without the mapping functionality, and I had fortestonly on the other patch that needed to be removed anyways.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "f3a13c632fffaff1fc8d292a3544c56f1c33a8c7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-14 19:10:33.000000000",
      "message": "Abandoned\n\nThis was merged into http://review.whamcloud.com/9299 .",
